data.enText: being an essential part of sth

data.chText: 音乐是这所学校的课程中基本的一环。
data.enText: Music is an integral part of the school's curriculum.

data.chText: 这门课程也包括实践经验。
data.enText: Practical experience is integral to the course.
included as part of sth, rather than supplied separately

data.chText: 所有型号都有内置的激光唱片机。
data.enText: All models have an integral CD player.
having all the parts that are necessary for sth to be complete

simple_means.memory_skill: integr 完整 + al …的 → 完整的

tr: the result of a mathematical integration
F(x) is the integral of f(x) if dF/dx = f(x)
lacking nothing essential especially not damaged
example: a local motion keepeth bodies integral"- Baco
was able to keep the collection entire during his lifetime
fought to keep the union intact

tr: existing as an essential constituent or characteristic
example: the Ptolemaic system with its built-in concept of periodicity
a constitutional inability to tell the truth

tr: of or denoted by an integer

value.def: Something that is an integral part of something is an essential part of that thing.

example.ex: Rituals and festivals form an integral part of every human society...
example.tran: 仪式与节日构成了任何人类社会不可缺少的一部分。

example.ex: Anxiety is integral to the human condition.
example.tran: 焦虑是人类的基本生存状况之一。

value.tran: 基本的;构成整体所必需的
